From creaky wardrobe hinges in Rajbagh to a misaligned front door in Nowgam, carpentry jobs are among the most common home repairs in Srinagar. Knowing when to call a professional — and how to book one quickly — saves time and prevents small problems from becoming expensive fixes.

## Common carpentry jobs in Srinagar homes

- **Furniture repair** — broken chair legs, loose table joints, damaged drawers
- **Door and window fitting** — alignment, lock changes, weather stripping
- **Custom shelves and cabinets** — kitchen storage, study units, TV wall units
- **Bed and wardrobe assembly** — flat-pack furniture from local shops or online orders
- **Hinge, handle, and lock fixes** — kitchen cabinets, main gates, bathroom doors

Many Srinagar flats and houses use wooden doors and built-in furniture that need periodic maintenance, especially after humid seasons when wood expands and contracts.

## When to book a carpenter vs DIY

A loose screw or sticky drawer can often be fixed at home. Call a professional when:

- Hinges are stripped or doors no longer close properly
- Structural joints in furniture are cracked or wobbly
- You need precise measurements for custom work
- Locks or handles need replacement with matching hardware
- Water damage has affected wooden frames or panels

Attempting complex repairs without the right tools can damage doors, frames, or expensive furniture.

## What to expect from a Panun Kaergar carpenter

Verified carpenters on Panun Kaergar arrive with standard tools for on-site work. For custom projects, share photos and measurements when booking so the provider can advise on materials and timeline.

Typical visits include assessment, repair or installation, and basic cleanup. For larger jobs — full kitchen cabinet work or multiple doors — discuss scope and pricing upfront.

## Same-day carpentry in Srinagar

Same-day slots are available when a verified carpenter is free in your area. Bemina, Lal Chowk, Hyderpora, Soura, and Hazratbal are among the neighbourhoods we serve regularly. Book early in the day for the best chance of same-day service.

## Tips for getting a fair quote

Share clear photos of the damage or the space where work is needed. Mention door dimensions, wood type if known, and whether you already have replacement hardware. This helps the carpenter arrive prepared and avoids surprise costs on site.

